The code includes a clear docstring and brief comments, but it is cluttered with numerous unnecessary wildcard and duplicate imports which harm readability and style (score 0.6). The core algorithm is concise and optimal (O(n) time, O(k) space), so it is simple and efficient aside from import clutter (score 0.8). The implementation properly handles edge cases (e.g., len(nums) < k), maintains counts correctly, and worked under large inputs in tests, making it robust, though maintainability is slightly reduced by the import noise (score 0.9).
